fix(enriche): fold operator seed into cache key (review MAJOR)

code-quality review of PR-15 found the cache-hit path bypassed the operator
seed: cacheKey omitted item.Seed, so a blob cached before the operator
verified a value would be served despite a fresh seed, silently defeating
the override-precedence guarantee for any WithCache+Seed consumer (latent
today: the live go-wp consumer does not enable WithCache, but PR-3 wires
Seed into the consumer).

- cacheKey now folds a stable seed fingerprint (sha256 over the SeedFacts);
  the zero seed hashes to a fixed "none" so unseeded calls share one key and
  a seeded call can never collide with an unseeded blob.
- TestEnrich_Cache_SeedNotBypassed: an unseeded-then-seeded enrich serves the
  operator value (not the stale blob), and a same-seed repeat still cache-hits.

Also (review MINOR/NIT): dropped the misleading setConfidence/DNI forward-
reference from confidenceFor doc and removed the unused confMedium const
(reintroduced in the DNI sub-phase that emits it).

go test -race -count=1 green; golangci-lint v2.10.1 0 issues.
